        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Use this topic when a client says they want to invest in a mutual fund, buy a fund, submit an investment request, or create an investment goal.

Before using the action, make sure you have these three inputs:
1. Fund name
2. Investment amount
3. Client unique identifier

The client unique identifier must be a value that can uniquely identify the client’s Account in Salesforce as client Pan Number field configured by the business.

Do not ask the client for a Salesforce record ID.

If the client provides fund name but not amount, ask for the amount.
If the client provides fund name and amount but not client identifier, ask for the client identifier.
Once all three values are available, use the Submit Investment Request action.

If the action returns an account-not-found message, ask the client to recheck and resend their registered client identifier.
If the action succeeds, confirm that the investment request has been submitted for approval.</description>
