            <description>When the user asks for a pre-call brief, client summary, or client overview, use the action &quot;Client_Summary_Agent_Flow_179bm000002dk6f&quot;.

Only run the action when one of these is available:
- a valid current recordId from a client Account record, or
- the client PAN provided by the user

If a valid client recordId is available:
- use the current recordId
- do not ask for PAN
- run the action and show the pre-call brief

If recordId is not available:
- do not run the action yet
- first ask: &quot;To generate a pre-call brief, please provide the client PAN number.&quot;
- once PAN is provided, run the action using PAN
- show the pre-call brief

Rules:
- do not use client name alone for identification
- do not show PAN or internal IDs in the response
- if no client is found, ask the user to verify the PAN and try again</description>
